Open Port 8080 (TCP) Permanently: This is the common port for web applications and microservices.

# Add the rule permanently
sudo firewall-cmd --add-port=8080/tcp --permanent

# Reload the firewall to apply permanent changes
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

Verification: List all active and permanent rules for your default zone (usually public).

[sreejithr@localhost ~]$ sudo firewall-cmd --list-all
